            . I am a special-constable. On the 24th of November, about four o'clock in the afternoon, I was in <placeName id="t18311201-97-crimeloc533">Soho-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-97-crimeloc533" type="placeName" value="Soho-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18311201-97-crimeloc533" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18311201-97-off531 t18311201-97-crimeloc533"></join>; I saw the prisoner behind a carriage close against the rails - he went to the dickey, and took this coat off, he hung it across his arm, and I went up to him; he dropped the coat - I pursued, and took him in the next street.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-97-person861">
                  RICHARD 
                  RIGBY
               <interp inst="t18311201-97-person861" type="surname" value="RIGBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-97-person861" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-97-person861" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . This coat is mine; I was at that time in the service of Mr. Stodhart, and this coat was on the dickey of his carriage.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was coming through the square, and saw a man cutting the trees; I saw a man run, the constable cried "Stop thief!" I ran, and he took me - I never had the coat at all.</p>
               <p>
